  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Rehabilitation and expansion of the Marouge Retreat Center</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Marouge Congreation</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is seeking to support Assemblies de la Grace in peacebuilding efforts and cultural exchange in Haiti by renovating the Marouge Retreat Center. Assemblies de la Grace is a network of 23 church congregations based in Port-au-Prince and spanning across the West, South and Central Plateau zones of Haiti. The congregations in this network of churches are extremely poor. Public meeting space is a rarity in Haiti, particularly after the 2010 earthquake. There has been no site in the greater Port-au-Prince area where Anabaptist congregations and other like-minded non-governmental organizations and/or community-based organizations can meet to share peacebuilding efforts and engage in cultural exchanges. The Marouge Retreat Center is a 20 year old facility managed by one of the congregations within the network; the Center has significantly deteriorated due to neglect and delayed maintenance. This site is currently being built to be a place for meetings, training and retreats for pastors and congregants of the Assemblies de la Grace Anabaptist network and for community members.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Workers have been hired to address construction related needs for the Center. A fence was built in early August of 2012 to ensure the site will be more hazard-resistant. Training on hazard-resistant techniques have begun and will continue through the entirety of the project.  Water and sewage have also been assessed for the new Center. A three-room caretaker house has been drafted for a security guard to live at the site and processes for a new latrine on the site have also begun.</narrative>
  </description>
